Vanarion (Latin Vanarionensis ) is a historic and titular diocese of the Roman Catholic Church. The seat of the bishopric was a Roman town called Vanarion, founded in the Roman Empire province of Mauretania Caesariensis, which has been tentatively identified with ruins at Ksar-Tyr in northern Algeria. At present the Catholic bishops are titular. Between 2005 and May 13, 2013 the Bishop of Vanariony was auxiliary bishop of Katowice, JÃ³zef Kupny, he was replaced by Prosper Balthazar Lyimo of Tanzania, in 2014.
